SIMPLE: inducer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inducer
<hw>In*du"cer</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, induces or incites.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Genetics)</fld>
<def>A substance which, when it contacts a living cell, causes the
activation of a gene; <as>as, non-metabolizable <ex>inducers</ex> are
useful for studying the kinetics of genetic control
systems</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inducible</ent>⟦br⟧
